    {
        "content": "<p>Perhaps someone could give me a clue to help me understand the motivation to use a category of surjections.</p>\n<p>For example, might we say, that since the image of a function has an equivalent definition as a surjection, we want to see the relationship between the surjection whose codomain is <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">I</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span></span></span>, and other surjections?</p>",
